00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
(Watch on KonFlix.vip)

1
00:00:36,077 --> 00:00:38,872
-Surprise!
-Surprise!

2
00:00:38,955 --> 00:00:39,956
Hello, son?

3
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:41,916
We're here at your brother's place.

4
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:43,168
Do you want to drop by?

5
00:00:44,878 --> 00:00:45,795
Babe…

6
00:00:45,879 --> 00:00:47,714
<i>Why are you being so noisy?</i>

7
00:00:50,633 --> 00:00:51,676
If I leave,

8
00:00:51,760 --> 00:00:54,179
how will you build a case
against the Moravianos?

9
00:00:54,262 --> 00:00:55,847
I'm sure I'll find a way.

10
00:00:57,474 --> 00:00:58,933
Hey!

11
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:02,479
-I'll cook.
-No, no.

12
00:01:07,025 --> 00:01:08,902
<i>I think we need to follow a new lead.</i>

13
00:01:11,362 --> 00:01:14,491
<i>Are you sure you won't betray us?</i>

14
00:01:14,574 --> 00:01:15,992
I have a family.

15
00:01:17,869 --> 00:01:20,371
I also have a family to protect!

16
00:01:24,459 --> 00:01:25,919
Please have mercy.

17
00:01:27,337 --> 00:01:28,588
My dear…

18
00:01:33,760 --> 00:01:35,678
I'll take care of it.

19
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:43,478
I don't want complications in our plans.

20
00:01:56,908 --> 00:01:57,826
Sir…

21
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:08,545
Unfortunately,

22
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:12,382
she grew up in my world.

23
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:34,571
Papa!

24
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:36,567
<i>Chiara? She looks so naive!</i>

25
00:04:40,738 --> 00:04:42,615
But you know Chiara,

26
00:04:42,699 --> 00:04:44,742
when I checked her profile,

27
00:04:45,868 --> 00:04:47,787
she looks so harmless.

28
00:04:47,870 --> 00:04:51,749
You know, I wouldn't wonder
and be surprised

29
00:04:51,833 --> 00:04:56,671
if she's nothing
but a second-rate, trying hard,

30
00:04:57,297 --> 00:04:59,173
spoiled brat!

31
00:05:00,049 --> 00:05:04,095
And just in case
Chiara knows what her parents are doing,

32
00:05:04,178 --> 00:05:06,264
specifically her father,

33
00:05:14,605 --> 00:05:17,567
Why do you keep targeting Chiara?

34
00:05:18,401 --> 00:05:19,777
To be honest,

35
00:05:19,861 --> 00:05:22,572
is it because Mikoy
still hasn't called you?

36
00:05:22,655 --> 00:05:23,906
And he's still not sure

37
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:26,200
if he wants to continue
the mission with us?

38
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:39,964
And this guy Mikoy?

39
00:05:40,048 --> 00:05:44,427
I don't see even the slightest bit
of proactiveness in him.

40
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,803
You know people like Mikoy,

41
00:05:45,887 --> 00:05:50,683
I feel like they'd rather choose
the easy way out than to fight.

42
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:52,977
Because he's weak.

43
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:56,272
And that's where you're wrong.

44
00:05:57,690 --> 00:05:58,691
Really?

45
00:05:58,775 --> 00:06:02,070
But why hasn't he called you until now?

46
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:03,488
He still hasn't made a decision.

47
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:08,701
Bok… You know, you're
even worse than those

48
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,704
boyfriends or girlfriends
or partners who ghost people!

49
00:06:13,081 --> 00:06:16,125
Anyway, maybe my delivery arrived.

50
00:06:16,751 --> 00:06:18,211
I'll be back.

51
00:06:37,814 --> 00:06:38,731
That's yours now.

52
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:41,526
That's my extra toothbrush, anyway.

53
00:06:41,609 --> 00:06:43,236
Instead of you borrowing mine.

54
00:07:05,049 --> 00:07:06,717
That girl is crazy!

55
00:07:08,761 --> 00:07:10,054
She didn't even say thank you?

56
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:14,517
I feel like I’ve been treated badly.

57
00:07:15,768 --> 00:07:17,103
And that's it?

58
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:20,940
And who was she, anyway?

59
00:07:23,025 --> 00:07:24,569
-I’ll ask Ma’am if she’s busy.
-Okay.

60
00:07:24,652 --> 00:07:25,945
Thank you.

61
00:07:26,028 --> 00:07:27,321
Ms. Tess!

62
00:07:28,239 --> 00:07:29,198
-Oh…
-Hello.

63
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,450
You know me?

64
00:07:31,033 --> 00:07:32,535
Actually, I don’t.

65
00:07:33,202 --> 00:07:35,955
But because of those
boxes of cake you're carrying,

66
00:07:36,038 --> 00:07:37,748
I was able to guess.

67
00:07:40,209 --> 00:07:41,878
Are you Mikoy's friend?

68
00:07:41,961 --> 00:07:43,337
Uh, kind of…

69
00:07:43,421 --> 00:07:47,049
It’s something like that.
But Alex is actually the one he knows.

70
00:07:47,133 --> 00:07:51,179
But anyway, he mentioned
that your Cebu cake is really delicious!

71
00:07:51,262 --> 00:07:52,680
So we ended up ordering.

72
00:07:54,015 --> 00:07:56,809
Well then, here is your order delivery.

73
00:07:56,893 --> 00:07:59,729
Good thing we visited Mikoy.

74
00:07:59,812 --> 00:08:03,274
Rather than sending it by courier,
we just delivered it ourselves, right?

75
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:06,319
-Yes.
-I'm sure Alex will be happy about that.

76
00:08:09,197 --> 00:08:10,573
What's your name, son?

77
00:08:11,365 --> 00:08:12,700
Sianong, sir!

78
00:08:12,783 --> 00:08:14,035
And what is your name?

79
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:17,705
I’m Mikoy's father, Mario.

80
00:08:17,788 --> 00:08:19,373
Oh, right.

81
00:08:19,457 --> 00:08:21,042
Oh, just a second.

82
00:08:27,381 --> 00:08:29,217
Here's the payment,

83
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,134
-Oh!
-Ms. Tess.

84
00:08:30,218 --> 00:08:32,386
Thank you very much!

85
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:33,596
Oh my!

86
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:35,139
This is too much.

87
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:36,307
It's okay!

88
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:39,852
This was even a special delivery from you.
So the extra there is your tip.

89
00:08:39,936 --> 00:08:42,188
-Thank you very much!
-You even went through the trouble.

90
00:08:44,315 --> 00:08:47,401
Sianong… What kind of agency is this?

91
00:08:49,111 --> 00:08:52,990
We're the agency that handles
transnational crimes,

92
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:58,496
especially for us Filipinos
who face crimes while abroad.

93
00:08:59,455 --> 00:09:03,543
So you're an investigator? Police?

94
00:09:19,225 --> 00:09:21,978
-Just kidding, sir!
-You're too much!

95
00:09:22,061 --> 00:09:23,896
-I was just kidding! You…
-You're too much.

96
00:09:23,980 --> 00:09:26,023
Just to make our morning fun!

97
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:27,233
-Just kidding. It’s something like that.
-I see.

98
00:09:27,316 --> 00:09:28,442
We're police officers.

99
00:09:29,360 --> 00:09:31,195
Will we be able to meet Alex?

100
00:09:32,863 --> 00:09:35,032
She has a meeting.

101
00:09:35,116 --> 00:09:36,742
But please don't worry, Ms. Tess.

102
00:09:36,826 --> 00:09:38,202
I'll personally tell her

103
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:39,829
that you were the ones
who brought this here.

104
00:09:39,912 --> 00:09:41,706
Thank you very much, okay?

105
00:09:41,789 --> 00:09:43,249
You're welcome.

106
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:45,668
Oh, I'll head out first, okay?

107
00:09:45,751 --> 00:09:47,336
-Sure.
-Goodbye, Ms. Tess.

108
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:48,629
Mr. Mario and…

109
00:09:48,713 --> 00:09:49,589
I’m Betchay.

110
00:09:49,672 --> 00:09:50,548
Betchay, okay!

111
00:09:50,631 --> 00:09:52,008
-Betchay.
-Hello. Good morning.

112
00:09:52,091 --> 00:09:53,676
-All right!
-There’s the cake.

113
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,635
-Okay.
-All right.

114
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,178
-Okay.
-Thank you!

115
00:09:56,262 --> 00:09:57,263
-Please take the cakes.
-Thank you, miss.

116
00:09:57,346 --> 00:09:58,180
-Okay, thank you.
-Okay!

117
00:09:58,264 --> 00:10:00,057
-Take care!
-We got a tip!

118
00:10:00,141 --> 00:10:01,684
See, I told you.

119
00:10:01,767 --> 00:10:03,519
We have extra profit!

120
00:10:04,353 --> 00:10:05,730
No way. That's too expensive!

121
00:10:05,813 --> 00:10:07,023
Just get some ice cream.

122
00:10:07,106 --> 00:10:09,692
-Ice cream.
-Come on!

123
00:10:31,172 --> 00:10:34,592
There, sir. These are
our favorite drivers.

124
00:10:34,675 --> 00:10:36,093
-There…
-Sir, good afternoon.

125
00:10:36,177 --> 00:10:37,511
Hello, sir.

126
00:10:37,595 --> 00:10:38,721
Oh…

127
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:41,807
This little thing, it's nothing to them.

128
00:10:54,945 --> 00:10:56,864
<i>Mikoy Pinagpala…</i>

129
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:02,578
<i>I finally found you!</i>

130
00:11:08,042 --> 00:11:09,877
No problem, boss.

131
00:11:15,674 --> 00:11:16,842
If there's a problem,

132
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:18,636
don't hesitate to call me.

133
00:11:18,719 --> 00:11:20,262
-Yes, sir.
-Okay.

134
00:11:21,639 --> 00:11:24,183
Manager, Santos is late again.

135
00:11:24,266 --> 00:11:25,434
I don't know where he keeps going.

136
00:11:25,518 --> 00:11:27,603
He said there was traffic
on the road again.

137
00:11:28,562 --> 00:11:30,731
Oh! Boss, sorry!
I didn't realize you were there.

138
00:11:33,109 --> 00:11:35,027
No. It's fine.

139
00:11:36,529 --> 00:11:38,155
So, what's the problem here?

140
00:11:38,239 --> 00:11:39,698
Why is Santos always late?

141
00:11:39,782 --> 00:11:41,951
Oh, it's nothing, Boss!

142
00:11:42,034 --> 00:11:46,372
We have a container van that sometimes
arrives late at the port.

143
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:47,832
So most of the time,

144
00:11:47,915 --> 00:11:50,501
the drivers sleep at the stopover.

145
00:11:50,584 --> 00:11:51,669
Or sometimes,

146
00:11:51,752 --> 00:11:56,048
for whatever reason,
the trip gets delayed.

147
00:11:56,132 --> 00:12:00,136
We have a theory in the office
about how the cargo is being moved.

148
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:02,304
<i>While the container vans</i>
<i>are on their way to the port,</i>

149
00:12:02,388 --> 00:12:05,933
<i>some of them take a different route</i>
<i>to switch the cargo.</i>

150
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:08,602
That’s normal, sir.

151
00:12:12,106 --> 00:12:14,108
Give me a report about it.

152
00:12:14,191 --> 00:12:16,527
I just want to know
if we can help our drivers.

153
00:12:17,486 --> 00:12:18,988
Oh, Boss!

154
00:12:19,071 --> 00:12:21,073
Don't worry about it.
I'll take care of it!

155
00:12:21,157 --> 00:12:23,325
Those drivers are just stubborn.

156
00:12:23,409 --> 00:12:25,244
I'll be the one to discipline them.

157
00:12:44,305 --> 00:12:45,139
Hey! Get inside!

158
00:12:45,723 --> 00:12:46,557
-Hey! Hey!
-Get inside!

159
00:12:46,640 --> 00:12:47,516
-Oh!
-Don't be noisy!

160
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:48,434
-Okay.
-Get in!

161
00:12:48,517 --> 00:12:50,019
-Okay, wait.
-Hurry up!

162
00:12:50,102 --> 00:12:51,061
Get in!

163
00:12:55,983 --> 00:12:56,817
Get in!

164
00:12:59,653 --> 00:13:01,238
Look, guys!

165
00:13:01,947 --> 00:13:03,365
Sweet cake from Cebu.

166
00:13:03,449 --> 00:13:04,366
PINAGPALA
SPECIAL BAKESHOP

167
00:13:04,450 --> 00:13:07,286
This was freshly baked
just three days ago.

168
00:13:07,369 --> 00:13:08,329
Okay?

169
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:10,539
You could say it's like an antique,

170
00:13:10,623 --> 00:13:13,167
but it has a modern taste.

171
00:13:13,792 --> 00:13:15,002
-Looks delicious.
-And according to

172
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:17,296
the Association of All Gym Goers,

173
00:13:17,379 --> 00:13:20,466
this is public enemy number one.

174
00:13:20,549 --> 00:13:22,635
Because it ruins your diet.

175
00:13:22,718 --> 00:13:25,429
It’s so delicious, you can't resist it,
even if you’re a gym goer.

176
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,056
You know that feeling?

177
00:13:27,139 --> 00:13:29,767
It’s addictive! So, look! Try it!

178
00:13:29,850 --> 00:13:31,977
-Come on! Dara! Come on! Try! Dara!
-Look, he's enjoying it.

179
00:13:32,061 --> 00:13:33,729
Go ahead! Come on!

180
00:13:39,527 --> 00:13:42,321
So delicious! Delicious! So good!

181
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:43,822
Feels like heaven!

182
00:13:50,913 --> 00:13:53,165
What happened to your faces?

183
00:13:55,292 --> 00:13:56,293
I get it.

184
00:13:56,377 --> 00:13:58,128
It’s really delicious, right?

185
00:13:58,212 --> 00:14:01,048
It’s so delicious,
you just end up speechless.

186
00:14:01,131 --> 00:14:01,966
Right, Dara?

187
00:14:03,175 --> 00:14:06,303
Or maybe you’re acting that way

188
00:14:07,638 --> 00:14:09,014
because the boss is behind me.

189
00:14:09,098 --> 00:14:11,600
And he's jealous of us!

190
00:14:19,650 --> 00:14:20,985
You want some cake, sir?

191
00:14:23,153 --> 00:14:24,154
Sianong…

192
00:14:25,239 --> 00:14:26,699
In my office.

193
00:14:27,741 --> 00:14:29,034
Alex!

194
00:14:33,956 --> 00:14:35,583
Let’s clean up.

195
00:14:37,084 --> 00:14:38,294
-Go ahead.
-Here.

196
00:14:38,377 --> 00:14:39,545
Hurry up!

197
00:14:39,628 --> 00:14:41,338
Wait! Easy, bro!

198
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:42,756
Who are you?

199
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:45,050
Wait, what do you need?

200
00:14:45,134 --> 00:14:46,760
Wait, is this a hold-up?

201
00:14:46,844 --> 00:14:48,137
Bro, I’m not rich, okay?

202
00:14:48,220 --> 00:14:49,763
And I just started working here.

203
00:14:49,847 --> 00:14:51,557
And this car, this is not mine!

204
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,225
This is just a company car. Promise!

205
00:14:53,309 --> 00:14:54,351
What is this?

206
00:14:54,435 --> 00:14:55,769
Some amateur acting school?

207
00:14:55,853 --> 00:14:58,063
Pretending like you
don’t know anything? Hey!

208
00:14:58,147 --> 00:15:00,357
Don’t act smart!

209
00:15:00,441 --> 00:15:02,610
If it weren’t for you,

210
00:15:02,693 --> 00:15:04,445
my brother would still be alive!

211
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:06,447
Huh? Hold on!

212
00:15:06,530 --> 00:15:07,948
What are you talking about?

213
00:15:08,032 --> 00:15:10,701
And how am I involved
in your brother's death?

214
00:15:10,784 --> 00:15:13,412
Also, an important question,
who is your brother?

215
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:17,791
Just a moment.

216
00:15:20,628 --> 00:15:21,837
Can you press on the photos?

217
00:15:23,672 --> 00:15:24,924
Press it.

218
00:15:26,091 --> 00:15:27,551
There. Right there.

219
00:15:29,053 --> 00:15:30,638
-Him!
-Huh?

220
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:33,974
He’s handsome.

221
00:15:35,517 --> 00:15:36,685
Wait.

222
00:15:42,816 --> 00:15:44,860
We’re twins. He’s my brother.

223
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:48,364
That explains it.

224
00:15:49,114 --> 00:15:51,909
Literally, the spitting image
of each other.

225
00:15:51,992 --> 00:15:55,621
But if you ask me,
you look better than him.

226
00:15:55,704 --> 00:15:58,832
-Just a little, okay?
-Are you joking?

227
00:15:58,916 --> 00:16:01,043
If you’re joking, it’s not funny!

228
00:16:01,126 --> 00:16:02,336
Huh!

229
00:16:02,419 --> 00:16:04,171
I’m sorry! Come on.

230
00:16:04,254 --> 00:16:05,506
I just want you to relax.

231
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:08,634
Because you might
do something you’ll regret.

232
00:16:08,717 --> 00:16:10,260
I’ll regret?!

233
00:16:10,344 --> 00:16:12,179
If anyone should regret anything,

234
00:16:12,262 --> 00:16:13,931
it’s that Czech Viktor guy!

235
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:15,599
That bald one!

236
00:16:15,683 --> 00:16:17,351
I’m his nightmare!

237
00:16:17,434 --> 00:16:18,894
In English…

238
00:16:22,064 --> 00:16:23,941
I’m going to kill you first.

239
00:16:24,024 --> 00:16:25,567
To send a message to Viktor

240
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:29,571
that he will be the next one
I’ll take down for my brother!

241
00:16:30,781 --> 00:16:34,952
NORBERTO S. RUIZ

242
00:16:39,373 --> 00:16:42,167
Tell me, Agent Alex and Agent Sianong.

243
00:16:42,251 --> 00:16:48,048
Did I imagine seeing
Mikoy’s parents here in our office?

244
00:16:48,632 --> 00:16:51,093
The parents of our very own asset?

245
00:16:53,470 --> 00:16:55,639
Actually, sir, it was my idea.

246
00:16:57,057 --> 00:17:00,894
And your idea was to order
and have the cake delivered?

247
00:17:07,484 --> 00:17:09,987
Because we received
a credible threat to his life.

248
00:17:17,411 --> 00:17:19,329
But for reasons unknown to us,

249
00:17:19,413 --> 00:17:21,623
he did not answer our calls.

250
00:17:21,707 --> 00:17:23,959
And because of that,

251
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:27,588
I called their bakery’s direct hotline

252
00:17:27,671 --> 00:17:29,590
and pretended to be a customer.

253
00:17:30,340 --> 00:17:36,847
I didn’t expect that his mom and dad
would personally deliver it to our office.

254
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:39,933
You two are becoming very careless.

255
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:45,439
Don’t do anything
that could ruin your mission, okay?

256
00:17:49,234 --> 00:17:51,403
Do you have a full profile of the parents?

257
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:54,239
Uh, yes, sir.

258
00:17:54,323 --> 00:17:57,743
And as far as I know,
there are no red flags.

259
00:17:57,826 --> 00:17:59,578
They are just simple people.

260
00:18:01,538 --> 00:18:02,831
Are you sure?

261
00:18:02,915 --> 00:18:04,374
Yes, sir.

262
00:18:06,168 --> 00:18:07,294
Why, sir?

263
00:18:07,377 --> 00:18:09,088
Do we have a problem?

264
00:18:10,339 --> 00:18:12,674
Do you know these people?

265
00:18:19,014 --> 00:18:21,767
Okay. Okay.

266
00:18:21,850 --> 00:18:25,854
But before anything else,
before you kill me, let's break that down.

267
00:18:25,938 --> 00:18:27,439
First,

268
00:18:28,857 --> 00:18:30,317
before calling him bald,

269
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:32,486
we know he has lost his hair.

270
00:18:32,569 --> 00:18:34,822
We don’t need to call him bald, right?

271
00:18:34,905 --> 00:18:37,324
We don’t even know
what he’s going through.

272
00:18:37,407 --> 00:18:39,118
That’s why his hair doesn’t grow back.

273
00:18:39,201 --> 00:18:40,786
-Is that so?
-Come on. Yes!

274
00:18:40,869 --> 00:18:42,037
Sorry about that.

275
00:18:44,498 --> 00:18:45,916
There you go!

276
00:18:45,999 --> 00:18:47,000
Seriously!

277
00:18:48,210 --> 00:18:49,169
Second,

278
00:18:49,253 --> 00:18:51,171
if you really want to get back at him,

279
00:18:51,839 --> 00:18:54,842
why do you need to kill me
to send him a message? Right?

280
00:18:54,925 --> 00:18:56,593
Just go straight to him.

281
00:18:56,677 --> 00:18:58,178
Go straight to the point!

282
00:18:58,262 --> 00:18:59,888
No more beating around the bush!

283
00:18:59,972 --> 00:19:03,392
And third, if you really
want to get back at him,

284
00:19:03,475 --> 00:19:05,227
don’t kill me.

285
00:19:05,310 --> 00:19:08,272
Because honestly, I can actually help you.

286
00:19:08,355 --> 00:19:10,190
Believe it or not,

287
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:17,406
What do you mean by that?

288
00:19:24,163 --> 00:19:27,457
Send me again
the full profile of his family.

289
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:30,961
And make sure
you stay away from his family.

290
00:19:31,044 --> 00:19:35,883
We don’t want any more innocent people
getting caught up in this mess.

291
00:19:38,135 --> 00:19:39,511
Copy, sir.

292
00:19:47,853 --> 00:19:48,770
Okay, sir.

293
00:19:55,652 --> 00:19:58,947
<i>We should not proceed with the demolition!</i>

294
00:19:59,031 --> 00:20:01,658
<i>There are innocent people within the area.</i>

295
00:20:01,742 --> 00:20:03,619
<i>Our mission is our mission.</i>

296
00:20:03,702 --> 00:20:06,955
<i>And we must achieve our objectives,</i>
<i>no matter what it takes!</i>

297
00:20:16,506 --> 00:20:18,717
You know, that girl is such a weirdo!

298
00:20:18,800 --> 00:20:21,094
Anyway, I just woke up,

299
00:20:21,178 --> 00:20:23,138
and she was already next to me in bed.

300
00:20:23,222 --> 00:20:25,015
It was like we were really roommates.

301
00:20:25,098 --> 00:20:27,309
Maybe she really is your roommate?

302
00:20:27,392 --> 00:20:31,063
No! Can I really have a roommate
without me knowing?

303
00:20:31,146 --> 00:20:32,731
And we’re all boys!

304
00:20:32,814 --> 00:20:35,776
You know what? Lock your door properly.

305
00:20:35,859 --> 00:20:37,611
So no one can just walk right in.

306
00:20:37,694 --> 00:20:39,196
I locked it!

307
00:20:39,279 --> 00:20:43,283
I have no idea how she still managed
to get into my room.

308
00:20:43,867 --> 00:20:45,994
So, what do you want?
Should we call the police?

309
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:48,664
The police, really?

310
00:20:49,539 --> 00:20:51,541
There’s no need. It’s too much hassle.

311
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:54,002
I don't want to go back
to the police station.

312
00:20:54,086 --> 00:20:56,588
You know that I'm already traumatized.

313
00:20:57,172 --> 00:20:59,758
If you want, let's just adopt a dog.

314
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:01,760
-Right?
-Oh!

315
00:21:01,843 --> 00:21:04,388
-It seems fun here.
-It's allowed.

316
00:21:06,223 --> 00:21:08,433
Bros, look who’s here.

317
00:21:14,022 --> 00:21:15,399
What do you mean?

318
00:21:16,149 --> 00:21:18,735
How can you help me against Viktor?

319
00:21:21,989 --> 00:21:25,117
Because I'm not just one
of Viktor's normal employees. Okay?

320
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:27,494
What do you mean you're not normal?

321
00:21:27,577 --> 00:21:28,662
Are you a paranormal?

322
00:21:28,745 --> 00:21:30,205
Are you messing with me?!

323
00:21:30,289 --> 00:21:32,582
No! Come on!

324
00:21:34,293 --> 00:21:36,503
It's just hard to explain.

325
00:21:36,586 --> 00:21:38,463
I can't exactly tell you.

326
00:21:38,547 --> 00:21:41,091
But anyway, I'm not your enemy, okay?

327
00:21:41,174 --> 00:21:43,552
Actually, I'm on your side.

328
00:21:45,595 --> 00:21:47,139
So, what are you saying?

329
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:51,810
You're some kind of police agent
who infiltrated Viktor's company?

330
00:21:51,893 --> 00:21:55,856
And you're the key to exposing
all of his criminal activities?

331
00:21:55,939 --> 00:21:58,859
The one who's going
to bring him down? Is that it?

332
00:22:00,485 --> 00:22:01,695
Yes.

333
00:22:01,778 --> 00:22:02,946
Something like that.

334
00:22:03,864 --> 00:22:04,698
You're good.

335
00:22:11,621 --> 00:22:13,165
I already have so many problems!

336
00:22:13,248 --> 00:22:15,042
And now you're adding to them!

337
00:22:15,125 --> 00:22:17,961
You know, you're such a funny guy!

338
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:22,549
It’s really a shame to kill you.

339
00:22:22,632 --> 00:22:25,218
Because the world would lose its joy.

340
00:22:25,302 --> 00:22:26,428
You know, if I were you,

341
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:28,889
I’d stop watching too much

342
00:22:28,972 --> 00:22:30,098
Jason Bourne!

343
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,683
James Bond!

344
00:22:31,767 --> 00:22:33,727
All sorts of things
are getting into your head!

345
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:36,188
I’m not lying, I promise!

346
00:22:36,271 --> 00:22:37,481
It’s true!

347
00:22:37,564 --> 00:22:40,317
I’m secretly working for the police.

348
00:22:40,901 --> 00:22:43,445
So if you’ll kill me, that’s it!

349
00:22:43,528 --> 00:22:45,655
Our whole operation will be ruined.

350
00:22:45,739 --> 00:22:47,407
We’ll never be able to bring Viktor down.

351
00:22:47,491 --> 00:22:49,284
Do you want that, huh?

352
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:57,793
Bro, what happened to you?

353
00:22:58,418 --> 00:23:00,295
Ever since you got out of jail,

354
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,297
you haven’t been hanging out with us.

355
00:23:03,090 --> 00:23:05,008
It makes me feel like

356
00:23:05,092 --> 00:23:07,177
you don’t want to be friends
with me anymore.

357
00:23:14,684 --> 00:23:15,685
Angelito.

358
00:23:16,728 --> 00:23:18,188
I’m having trouble with drafting.

359
00:23:19,689 --> 00:23:21,483
And I know you can help me.

360
00:23:21,566 --> 00:23:22,526
Right?

361
00:23:25,195 --> 00:23:27,197
Owen, I’m sorry, okay?

362
00:23:27,989 --> 00:23:31,034
I also have a lot of school requirements.

363
00:23:31,118 --> 00:23:32,577
I still have so much to finish.

364
00:23:37,499 --> 00:23:38,750
So, you’re rejecting me?

365
00:23:41,128 --> 00:23:43,171
You’re turning down my request?

366
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:46,049
It’s not like that, Owen.

367
00:23:48,343 --> 00:23:49,928
But you know,

368
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:55,934
you can’t always depend on others
for our course requirements.

369
00:23:57,269 --> 00:23:58,478
Honestly,

370
00:23:59,062 --> 00:24:01,523
you need to learn how
to figure things out yourself.

371
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:06,319
That’s why we’re here in school, right?

372
00:24:06,403 --> 00:24:07,696
To learn.

373
00:24:14,202 --> 00:24:15,328
To learn.

374
00:24:18,874 --> 00:24:20,792
All right. How about this?

375
00:24:22,085 --> 00:24:23,336
If you help me,

376
00:24:24,337 --> 00:24:26,006
we’ll be the best of friends.

377
00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:31,261
But if you won't help me,

378
00:24:33,597 --> 00:24:34,973
you might regret it.

379
00:24:37,225 --> 00:24:39,227
I expect my plates tomorrow, okay?

380
00:24:41,813 --> 00:24:42,772
Boys, let's go.

381
00:24:42,856 --> 00:24:44,024
-Let's go.
-Come on!

382
00:24:57,454 --> 00:24:59,122
Hey! Okay!

383
00:24:59,206 --> 00:25:00,373
If you pull that out,

384
00:25:00,957 --> 00:25:03,376
I'm going to shoot up your head!

385
00:25:03,460 --> 00:25:05,295
-Just relax!
-Do it slowly.

386
00:25:07,422 --> 00:25:08,590
Oh!

387
00:25:09,466 --> 00:25:10,800
You don't want to believe me.

388
00:25:10,884 --> 00:25:13,845
I just want to prove to you
that I'm telling the truth.

389
00:25:15,222 --> 00:25:19,392
Here it is. I’ll call
my police handler. Okay?

390
00:25:26,816 --> 00:25:28,693
Director Norberto is right.

391
00:25:28,777 --> 00:25:31,071
We shouldn’t involve Mikoy’s family.

392
00:25:31,905 --> 00:25:33,698
It doesn't matter, Bok.

393
00:25:33,782 --> 00:25:36,409
You know, as long
as Mikoy isn’t calling you,

394
00:25:36,493 --> 00:25:37,786
it doesn't really matter.

395
00:25:38,954 --> 00:25:41,748
But I can’t blame him either.

396
00:25:41,831 --> 00:25:43,708
This is really a tough job.

397
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:47,671
And the only ones who can spy
on syndicates like the Moravianos

398
00:25:47,754 --> 00:25:50,548
are the people who are strong and brave.

399
00:25:55,595 --> 00:25:58,473
-It’s Mikoy.
-Oh, go for it! What are you waiting for?

400
00:25:58,556 --> 00:26:00,267
Answer the call.

401
00:26:00,350 --> 00:26:02,185
-Hello?
-Hello?

402
00:26:02,269 --> 00:26:03,603
Special Agent Alex?

403
00:26:04,187 --> 00:26:05,063
This is Mikoy.

404
00:26:05,897 --> 00:26:07,857
Honestly, I didn’t expect you to call.

405
00:26:07,941 --> 00:26:10,443
But I’m very happy
to hear your voice again.

406
00:26:10,527 --> 00:26:12,153
Looks like we have a lot to talk about.

407
00:26:13,029 --> 00:26:14,489
Exactly!

408
00:26:14,572 --> 00:26:17,075
That’s why I really want to meet you.

409
00:26:17,867 --> 00:26:19,828
And bring a burger, okay?

410
00:26:19,911 --> 00:26:22,289
<i>And extra fries!</i>

411
00:26:22,372 --> 00:26:23,957
Sure! Where are you?

412
00:26:24,958 --> 00:26:26,793
Just here at the Annex parking.

413
00:26:27,377 --> 00:26:28,545
And hurry up!

414
00:26:29,129 --> 00:26:30,505
I’m starving!

415
00:26:31,131 --> 00:26:32,382
All right, no problem.

416
00:26:32,966 --> 00:26:34,175
Okay. Thank you!

417
00:26:38,221 --> 00:26:41,308
So, what happened? What’s the problem?

418
00:26:41,391 --> 00:26:42,475
Mikoy is in trouble.

419
00:26:42,559 --> 00:26:44,144
He just gave us a distress signal!

420
00:26:45,061 --> 00:26:46,813
Burger with extra fries!

421
00:26:47,397 --> 00:26:49,274
-Let’s go!
-We move in two minutes!

422
00:26:49,357 --> 00:26:50,608
We’re coming in hot!

423
00:26:51,985 --> 00:26:53,778
You know, that is impressive.

424
00:26:53,862 --> 00:26:56,448
After everything, he still remembered
his distress signal.

425
00:26:56,531 --> 00:26:58,450
So, stop underestimating him.

426
00:26:58,533 --> 00:27:00,035
Mikoy knows what he’s doing.

427
00:27:00,118 --> 00:27:02,078
He knows what kind of trouble
he’s getting into.

428
00:27:02,162 --> 00:27:03,288
So, let’s move quickly.

429
00:27:03,371 --> 00:27:05,623
We cannot afford anything
to happen to our asset.

430
00:27:05,707 --> 00:27:07,250
Okay! Let’s go!

431
00:27:07,334 --> 00:27:09,002
So, there you go.

432
00:27:09,085 --> 00:27:10,211
Do you believe it now?

433
00:27:10,879 --> 00:27:13,131
Agent Alex will explain it to you.

434
00:27:13,214 --> 00:27:15,258
What do you think of me?

435
00:27:15,342 --> 00:27:16,509
Stupid?

436
00:27:16,593 --> 00:27:17,802
You’re tricking me!

437
00:27:21,014 --> 00:27:22,265
I know what you did.

438
00:27:22,349 --> 00:27:23,433
That’s a code!

439
00:27:24,017 --> 00:27:26,728
Bring burger with extra fries?

440
00:27:26,811 --> 00:27:28,521
What do you think of me?

441
00:27:28,605 --> 00:27:30,148
Someone who doesn’t watch Netflix?

442
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:33,818
I know you called your men for backup!

443
00:27:33,902 --> 00:27:34,944
No!

444
00:27:35,028 --> 00:27:36,529
I just really love burgers!

445
00:27:36,613 --> 00:27:37,739
Promise!

446
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:40,742
If you really love burgers,
which tastes better,

447
00:27:40,825 --> 00:27:43,453
Burger McJo or Burger Queen?

448
00:27:44,037 --> 00:27:46,081
Huh? Huh?!

449
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:47,374
Answer!

450
00:27:50,377 --> 00:27:51,378
McJo?

451
00:27:52,379 --> 00:27:54,255
Wrong! There’s no right answer,

452
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:57,050
because both are delicious!

453
00:27:58,510 --> 00:27:59,677
Ahh! Hey!

454
00:27:59,761 --> 00:28:01,346
Hey, funny boy!

455
00:28:01,429 --> 00:28:02,514
Help!

456
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:03,765
Funny boy!

457
00:28:06,601 --> 00:28:08,436
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached…</i>

458
00:28:08,520 --> 00:28:10,522
<i>Mikoy, where are you?</i>

459
00:28:10,605 --> 00:28:12,816
<i>Why can’t I contact you?</i>

460
00:28:15,527 --> 00:28:17,654
<i>The subscriber cannot be reached…</i>

461
00:28:26,454 --> 00:28:28,206
Mikoy!

462
00:28:29,249 --> 00:28:32,293
Mikoy! Where are you?

463
00:28:33,753 --> 00:28:35,547
Mikoy!

464
00:28:40,760 --> 00:28:44,222
<i>You and I know we need to protect him.</i>

465
00:28:47,434 --> 00:28:51,146
And I don’t want him to get involved
in our plans here in the Philippines.

466
00:28:51,229 --> 00:28:55,942
He must never go into
the syndicates that do evil things.

467
00:28:58,111 --> 00:29:01,573
<i>But will he accept who you really are?</i>

468
00:29:06,035 --> 00:29:07,871
I want to fully commit on this mission.

469
00:29:07,954 --> 00:29:11,040
<i>I’m ready to help you</i>
<i>take down the Moravianos.</i>

